Title: TeamPulse — המנהל רואה את מה שחשוב
Author: Cursor + Claude Code Skill
Draft date: 2026-06-22
Contact: https://www.teampulse.io

=====

INT. OPEN-PLAN OFFICE - MORNING

A wall of glass separates a quiet office from a noisy bullpen. Inside, screens pulse with notifications. SLACK pings, EMAILS land, a CALENDAR turns red.

CUT TO:

INT. MANAGER'S DESK - CONTINUOUS

DANA, mid-30s, rubs her temples. Three monitors, 47 unread threads, a half-drunk coffee. Her eyes dart between windows.

DANA
(sighing)
I have thirty priorities. And zero focus.

She drags a window. Another one opens behind it. Her finger hovers — she clicks — and a generic dashboard returns a wall of metrics she didn't ask for.

CUT TO:

INT. HALLWAY - DAY

A colleague sprints past, headphones in. Another pauses at the printer, scrolling Slack on their phone. No one talks.

CUT TO:

INT. MANAGER'S DESK - LATER

A single dashboard, dark blue. The pulse of a heartbeat line steadies across the top. Three cards rise into frame, one after another:

CARD ONE
Budget review — Friday.

CARD TWO
Customer escalation — NOW.

CARD THREE
Hiring loop — open.

DANA
(softly, almost to herself)
Three things. That's all I needed.

The wordmark "TeamPulse" fades in. Below it, in soft indigo:

> רק מה שחשוב. אף פעם הרעש.

The cursor blinks once. A subtle pulse. End.
